cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DB 

This paper is about search and ranking methods for Web archives, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with large-scale data processing and storage, which falls under cs.DL and cs.DB. Finally, since the paper discusses the challenges of preserving and securing digital content, it could also be classified under cs.CR.
